      <description>In the inaugural episode, we explore the deep history of the commons — from medieval English common lands to the Diggers who dared to reclaim them. What did we lose, and what can we still rebuild?</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[
        <p><em>Show notes coming soon — once the audio is finalized (GAR-8).</em></p>
        <p>In the inaugural episode of Untethered, we explore the deep history of the commons — from medieval English common lands to the Diggers who dared to reclaim them.</p>
        <p><strong>Topics covered:</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li>The origins of the commons in pre-enclosure England</li>
          <li>Gerrard Winstanley and the Diggers (True Levellers)</li>
          <li>What the enclosure movement actually took from ordinary people</li>
          <li>How the idea of the commons lives on today — and why it matters</li>
        </ul>
      ]]></content:encoded>
    </item>

